snippet: Memories of overthrowing a dictatorship remain strong among the elders of Santiago de Cuba, the city where the fight began, but the younger generation is ready to move on.
abstract: Handful of Cuban revolutionaries are still alive in Santiago de Cuba, birthplace of revolution started by Fidel Castro and his followers against dictatorship of Fulgencio Batista; several discuss socialist ideologies that led them to fight against Batista, impact Castro government has had on generations of Cubans, and their hopes for an enduring political legacy.
lead_paragraph: Memories of overthrowing a dictatorship remain strong among the elders of Santiago de Cuba, the city where the fight began, but the younger generation is ready to move on.

headline.main: Cuban Revolutionaries Hope Their Legacy Won’t Fade Away
headline.print_headline: Heroes of Cuba’s Revolution Hope Their Legacy Endures
